==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Secernent
<hw>Se*cern"ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>secernens</ets>, p. pr.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>Secreting; secretory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Secernent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Secernent
<hw>Se*cern"ent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which promotes
secretion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A vessel in, or by means of,
which the process of secretion takes place; a secreting
vessel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Secernment</ent>⟦br⟧
